# Oblivio Compose UI and previews

## When this applies

- All composable UI under `eu.brrm.oblivio.ui` (components, feature screens, theme).

## Previews (required)

- Add at least one `@Preview` for **every** public or internal composable that **draws UI** (layouts, design-system widgets, and `*Screen` content).
- Prefer **light and dark** coverage:
  - Light: default preview or `OblivioTheme(darkTheme = false) { … }`
  - Dark: `@Preview(…, uiMode = Configuration.UI_MODE_NIGHT_YES)` and/or `OblivioTheme(darkTheme = true) { … }`
- Wrap previews in `OblivioTheme { … }` so colors and typography match the app.
- Do **not** use hardcoded user-visible copy in previews; use `stringResource` for text that mirrors production.

## Exemptions

- `*ViewModel.kt`, Hilt `*Module.kt`, and pure navigation wiring without its own layout do not need visual previews.
- `*Route.kt` composables that only forward to `*Screen` and collect ViewModel state may omit a dedicated preview if the corresponding `*Screen` is already fully previewed.

## New reusable components

- Add previews in the same file as the component or in a sibling `*Previews.kt` in the same package (see `OblivioComponentsPreviews.kt`).
